==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hydrocarbon
<hw>Hy`dro*car"bon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hydro-</ets>, 2 + <ets>carbon</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A compound containing only hydrogen and carbon,
as methane, benzene, etc.; also, by extension, any of their
derivatives.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Hydrocarbon burner</b></col>,
<col><b>furnace</b></col>, <col><b>stove</b></col></mcol>, <cd>a burner,
furnace, or stove with which liquid fuel, as petroleum, is
used.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hydrocarbonaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
